HEADWORD: Hyoscyamus
<hw>Hy`os*cy"a*mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
Gr. <?/; <?/ a sow, hog + <?/ a bean.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of poisonous plants of the Nightshade
family; henbane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The leaves of the black henbane
(<spn>Hyoscyamus niger</spn>), used in neuralgic and pectoral
troubles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

